     Rodimus could not be faulted, in all the laser fire and confusion
there were enemies everywhere! Laser fire all around, the smell of
ozone and charred metal was like thick smog in the air. As the first
wave passed over though, one thing became clear, there was only one
Cyclonus, commander of this invasion, and somewhere amidst the sweeps
there was scourge the master of the hunt. But what Rodimus was not
wrong about was the sheer number of them, and the power of them! 

     As the carnage built it became painfully obvious to anyone who had
fought Cyclonus in the past, that while he make look similar, this
reformatted Cyclonus was sleeker, more agile, and the damage his
missiles and cannons were doing were rivaling what Galvatron did on his
best days. 

The sweeps were cutting a devastating swath of wreckage through the
city as smoke rose to cover the sky in puffs of inky blackness. From
high above Cyclonus looked down and approved even as Scourge hovered
next to him. 

"You two!" Scourge's rough voice somehow managed to penetrate the
cacophony of the battle to reach Nighstrike and Darkfate . �You�re
coming with us!�

Without waiting for an answer Cyclonus, and Scourge banked twards the
Maximal base, even as several sweeps took up position around them,
their cannon fire laying waste to the front gates of the base as they
landed, renewed cannon fire giving them an entrance!

High overhead Sweeps continued the onslaught as they pressed their
attacks!

Preston
(Da'Minions)
